<http://www.spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/event/46001ANTMSCJPQGDHCBQLMJHRHSLVRCJM>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Crip Cinema (Guest Presentation)";
  schema:description """
	Calling all film lovers! <span class=\"BoldText\">The Disability Collective</span> is thrilled to introduce <span class=\"ItalicText\">Crip Cinema</span>, an afternoon of disability-centred film screenings at this year’s Disability Arts Festival. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In partnership with Voices with Impact, ‘Crip Cinema’ will feature a collection of short films with themes of disability and mental health across a wide range of genres including narrative, documentary, animation, dance and spoken word. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>All films feature closed captions and live audio description, ASL interpretation will be available at Front of House. The screenings will be a relaxed environment where attendees can come and go as needed, with a quiet space available in the venue. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are available in a Pay-What-You-Can format. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Join us at 2 PM on Saturday, August 8th at Tarragon Theatre for the accessible cinematic experience of your dreams!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">This is a Mask Required, ASL Interpreted, and Audio Described event. The screening is followed by a Q&A.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">If you have any accessibility needs please contact Patron Services: patronservices@tarragontheatre.com or call us at 416-531-1827.</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-08-08T14:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
